ANITA LAXMI NARAYAN SINGH V. LAXMI NARAIN SINGH [1992] INSC 91; AIR 1992 SC 1148; 1992 (2) SCR 316; 1992 (2) SCC 562; 1992 (2) JT 349; 1992 (1) SCALE 722 (24 March 1992)

 AHMADI, A.M. (J) AHMADI, A.M. (J) VENKATACHALLIAH, M.N. (J) JEEVAN REDDY, B.P. (J) 
CITATION: 1992 AIR 1148 1992 SCR (2) 316 1992 SCC (2) 562 JT 1992 (2) 349 1992 SCALE (1)722 
ACT:
 Hindu Marriage Act, 1955 :
 Section 13-Divorce-Petition by husband at Bombay-Wife required to travel a long distance to defend proceedings- Transfer petition by wife-Supreme Court directing sufficient expenses for wife's stay and travel expenses-Grant of meagre amount of wife by Family Court-Consequent inability of wife to attend proceedings-Ex-parte divorce decree in favour of husband-Held grant of meagre amount of wife resulted in denial of justice-Ex-parte decree of divorce set aside.
 
